<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "5B">
<servcat sctnbr = "05" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENCP70A5206021" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "02" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "1">
<title>
Countershaft Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENCP70A5206019">Input Shaft and Countershaft Assembly Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENCP70A5206016">Manual Transaxle Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention1>
<ptxt>
Using an inappropriate hydraulic press or bearing puller could cause personal injury.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Check that both the hydraulic press and bearing puller are capable of safely bearing a load of at least 5 tons (11,000 lbs).
</ptxt>
</attention1>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Supporting the gear on the concave side of the puller can cause damage to the gear.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Support the gear on the flat side of the puller.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A5206021001">
<title>
Disassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove left bearing cone (2) with 4th gear (3) from countershaft (1) using bearing puller (4) and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520054.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.237mm" ver = "01" gw = "151" gh = "103"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply bearing puller (5) to 2nd gear (4), and remove 3rd &#38; 4th gear spacer (2) and 3rd gear (3) together with 2nd gear from countershaft (1) using hydraulic press. Remove needle bearing from countershaft.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520055.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "47.360mm" ver = "01" gw = "149" gh = "117"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove 2nd gear synchronizer outer ring, center cone and inner ring.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using snap ring pliers (3), remove circlip (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A521028.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.645mm" ver = "01" gw = "137" gh = "124"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.886in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Low speed synchronizer sleeve
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply bearing puller (3) to 1st gear (2) and remove low speed synchronizer sleeve &#38; hub assembly (1) with 1st gear using hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520057.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "41.094mm" ver = "01" gw = "142" gh = "99"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disassemble low speed synchronizer sleeve &#38; hub assembly.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove 1st gear needle bearing from shaft.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove right bearing cone (2) using bearing puller (3), metal stick (1) and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520058.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "41.602mm" ver = "01" gw = "151" gh = "101"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A5206021002">
<title>
Reassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean all components thoroughly, inspect them for any abnormal condition and replace them with new ones if necessary.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
To ensure lubrication of countershaft (1), blow air into oil holes (2) as shown in figure and make sure that they are free from any obstruction.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A521029.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "35.168mm" ver = "01" gw = "190" gh = "83"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Fit low speed synchronizer sleeve (4) to hub (3), insert 3 keys (2) in it, and then set springs (1) at specified position as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Be sure to assemble sleeve and hub in correct direction. (No direction is specified to each key.)
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Low speed synchronizer keys and springs are the largest in size compared with those of high speed and 5th speed ones.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<spec>
<title>
Synchronizer key installation position
</title>
<ptxt>
“a” = “b”
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A521055.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "76.062mm" ver = "02" gw = "195" gh = "199"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "0.966in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "0.986in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[A]: 
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
1st gear side
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[B]: 
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Short flange
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install right bearing cone (1) to countershaft (2) using special tool and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B019">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09923-78210">
09923–78210
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520062.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.508mm" ver = "01" gw = "177" gh = "129"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install needle bearing (4), apply oil to it, then install 1st gear and 1st gear synchronizer ring.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install low speed synchronizer sleeve &#38; hub assembly (1) using special tools and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Support shaft with special tool as shown in figure so that retainer of bearing cone will be free from compression.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Make sure that key slot (6) of synchronizer ring (2) are aligned with keys (5) while press-fitting sleeve &#38; hub assembly.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Check free rotation of 1st gear (3) after press-fitting sleeve &#38; hub assembly.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B020">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09923-78210">
09923–78210
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B021">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09925-18011">
09925–18011
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A521047.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "82.877mm" ver = "02" gw = "173" gh = "218"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "0.984in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "0.984in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[A]: 
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
1st gear side
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[B]: 
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Short flange
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Insert new circlip (1) securely.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install needle bearing (2), apply oil to it.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install 2nd gear synchronizer outer ring (3), center cone (4), inner ring (5) and 2nd gear (6) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RS0B521043.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "75.046mm" ver = "01" gw = "167" gh = "196"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.108in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[A]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Section A – A
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Press-fit 3rd gear (1) using special tools and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B022">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09923-78210">
09923–78210
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B023">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-84510">
09913–84510
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RS0B521044.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "47.215mm" ver = "01" gw = "74" gh = "117"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Press-fit spacer (1) and 4th gear (2) using special tools and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B024">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09923-78210">
09923–78210
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B025">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-84510">
09913–84510
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RS0B521045.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "47.587mm" ver = "01" gw = "81" gh = "118"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install left bearing cone (1) using special tools and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
For protection of right bearing cone (2), support shaft with special tool as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B026">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09923-78210">
09923–78210
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B027">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09925-98221">
09925–98221
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RS0B521046.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "44.585mm" ver = "01" gw = "96" gh = "110"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
